# Jira Post-Execution Comments

## The Rule

After every Jira write operation (create, edit, transition, label update, link), call `addCommentToJiraIssue` on each affected item to leave a timestamped comment summarising what was done and why.

This runs as the final step of EXECUTE, before VERIFY.

---

## What to Include in the Comment

Include every section that is relevant to the action taken. Omit sections that don't apply.

```
## Agent action — <YYYY-MM-DD>

**Triage session:** `triage-YYYY-MM-DD-NNN`

### What was done
- <Concise bullet list of every change made to this item: fields set, labels applied, links created, status transitioned, etc.>

### Why
- <Reasoning grounded in system design docs and/or current Jira state. No unsupported claims.>

### Implementation details (if work was implemented)
- Files changed: <list of files modified or created, with one-line description of each change>
- Key decisions: <any architectural or design choices made during implementation, with brief rationale>
- Known limitations / TODOs: <anything deferred or left incomplete, with a reference to the tracking item if one exists>

### Tests (if tests were written or run)
- Test files: <paths to new or modified test files>
- Coverage: <what scenarios are covered>
- Result: <pass / fail / skipped — with brief note if not all green>

### Commit(s)
- <git commit hash and message for any commits that relate to this item>

### Linked decisions
- <Path to any `docs/decisions/<slug>.md` file that was created or approved as part of this work, if applicable>
```

---

## When to Add the Comment

| Trigger | Comment required? |
|---|---|
| New item created via triage | Yes — on the newly created item |
| Existing item labels/priority updated | Yes — on the updated item |
| Story or Task implemented (code written) | Yes — on the Story/Task, include implementation details and tests sections |
| Spike closed / Decision Record approved | Yes — on the Spike, link to the decision doc |
| Item transition (e.g. In Progress → Done) | Yes — brief comment noting the transition and what was completed |
| VERIFY finds a gap and deferred item created | Yes — on the deferred item, quote the gap that was found |

---

## Format Rules

- Use the exact template above. Omit sections that have no content — do not leave empty section headers.
- Dates use `YYYY-MM-DD` format.
- Commit hashes should be the short form (7 chars).
- If multiple items are affected in one run, each gets its own comment. Do not write one combined comment across items.
- Comments are append-only. Do not edit previous agent comments.
